# 詞: 銀包

1. 佢家有好多銀包藏在庫房裡面，真係好富有。 (His family has many silver ingots stored in the warehouse; they are really wealthy.)
2. 銀包唔好直接暴露喺外頭，要好好保管。 (Don’t expose the silver ingots outside; they must be kept safe.)
3. 去古市場可以見到老先輩用銀包換食物。 (At the old market, you can see elders exchanging silver ingots for food.)
4. 銀包值錢好重，唔好輕易搬動。 (Silver ingots are very valuable and heavy; don’t move them carelessly.)
5. 唔使買銀包，佢都用現金買樣樣嘢。 (He doesn’t need to buy silver ingots; he just uses cash to buy everything.)
6. 銀包可以當作備用貨幣，真係好靠護。 (Silver ingots can be used as reserve currency; they are really reliable.)
7. 哋個商人用銀包作為交易儀式。 (That merchant uses silver ingots as part of the transaction ceremony.)
8. 銀包儲存得唔好，否則易生霉。 (Silver ingots must be stored properly, otherwise they can get rusty.)
9. 喺古時候，銀包係財富最好見得出嘅。 (Back in the old days, silver ingots were the most visible form of wealth.)
10. 唔諗到銀包可以鑄造成各種器物，真係好神妙。 (I didn’t realize that silver ingots can be melted down to make various items; it’s really amazing.)

---

